  <li id="comment-9874" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=1375#comment-9874"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-11-17T22:06:00-05:00">Saturday, November 17, 2007 at 10:06 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Julie, you certainly could make them ahead, but they really are best when they&#8217;re still warm from the oven, within the first half hour or hour at most.  They&#8217;re really quick to make, so what I do is this: when the turkey is about to come out of the oven, I start making the biscuits.  Then, as soon as it comes out, I slide the biscuits in.  They bake while the turkey rests before carving.  The timing usually works out perfectly.</></>Hope that helps!</p>
    </div>

