    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Perking up the boring carrot soup:</></>chop an onion and soften in olive oil on low heat.  Chop a large handful of fresh spinach, a few fresh mushrooms, and two or three red potatoes with the skin on.  If you have some pureed butternut squash to add, so much the better.  Add carrot soup, a sprinkle of cinnamon, and a heavy sprinkle of pepper.  Cook until potatoes are done.</p>
    </div>

